@node DESCRIPTION "ALI · Description"
Description
===========
  AmIRC log files don't look very well in text format, so decided to write
  a little tool, which solve this problem...

  @{" Features " link FEATURES}
  @{" Usage    " link USAGE}
@endnode

@node FEATURES "ALI · Features"
Features
========
  - MUI based
  - Automatic mode
  - Setable
    - Log-Format
    - Log-Dir
    - Colors

  @{" Description  " link DESCRIPTION}
  @{" Usage        " link USAGE}
@endnode

@node INSTALL "ALI · Installation"
Installation
============
  Installation is very simple.
  Just drag the ALI-drawer where you like, it does not need assigns.

  @{" Requirements " link REQUIREMENTS}
@endnode

@node REQUIREMENTS "ALI · Requirements"
Requirements
============
  - AmigaOS 3.x / MorphOS v1.x
  - NList classes
  - AmIRC log files

  @{" Installation " link INSTALL}
@endnode

@node USAGE "ALI · Usage"
Usage
=====
  On the first start of the tool, the file Default.AmIRCfg is parsed and
  converted into the inital ALI settings. Open the settings via the menu
  and adjust for your needs.

  Now select the file you want to view viathe popup gadget...


  ToolTypes
  ---------
  TOOLPRI/K/N - Set to toolpri from -127 to 127, defaults to 0
@endnode

